Building a well-behaved multi-threaded desktop application has been a hard task for many years, however it does not have to be that way anymore. The following sections explain the threading facilities exposed by the Griffon framework.

{note}
Prior to version 0.9.2 Controller actions were called in the same thread that published the event; most of the times this thread would be the UI thread. From 0.9.2 and onwards Controller actions will be executed outside of the UI thread. This feature can be [disabled|guide:disableThreadingInjection] altogether or in a per case basis as explained in the [Actions and Threads|guide:actionsAndThreads] section.
{note}